// =============================================================================
// adx_seed.kql — synthetic data seeding for the detection-diary KQL tests
// Author:    Jarmi
// Date:      2026-05-08
// Purpose:   Populate the schema created by adx_bootstrap.kql with handcrafted
//            positive and negative rows for every KQL rule in days/*/kql/.
//            Each block is annotated with the rule it exercises and the
//            expected hit count, so adx_tests.kql can assert determinism.
// Convention:
//            DeviceId  = d-<dayN>-<seq>     so rows are easy to filter per rule
//            Hostnames = WIN-<dayN>-<seq>   for Windows / WIN11
//                        LIN-<dayN>-<seq>   for Linux
//            All timestamps are within the last 6 days so default `ago(7d)`
//            filters in the rules pick them up.
// =============================================================================

